Mexican Stocks: Banorte, Maxcom Shares Climb; Grupo Mexico Drops

-- B y   J o n a t h a n   J .   L e v i n
-- 
2011-04-11T14:53:48Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-11/mexican-stocks-banorte-maxcom-shares-climb-grupo-mexico-drops.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in  Mexico  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 10:13 a.m. New York time.  The IPC index rose 0.3 percent to 37,591.10.  Grupo Financiero Banorte SAB (GFNORTEO MM), Mexico’s third-
largest bank by outstanding loans, rose 0.8 percent to 60 pesos.
The lender will exchange shares on April 15 as part of its
purchase of Ixe Grupo Financiero SAB, according to an April 8
statement to the Mexican stock exchange.  Grupo Mexico (GMEXICOB MM) slipped 0.4 percent to 43.25
pesos. Peru’s Energy & Mines Ministry rejected an environmental
impact study for a proposed $900 million copper project
presented by  Southern Copper , a Grupo Mexico SAB unit, according
to an April 8 e-mailed statement.  Maxcom Telecomunicaciones SAB (MAXCOMCP MM), Mexico’s
fifth-largest landline phone carrier, gained 3.3 percent to 6.21
pesos. Telefonica SA and Megacable Holdings SAB are competing to
buy Maxcom Telecomunicaciones SA for more than $110 million,
Excelsior newspaper’s Dario Celis said today in a column,
without saying where he got the information. Manuel Perez,
Maxcom’s investor relations manager, told Bloomberg News today
he had no information about sale talks.  To contact the reporters on this story:
Jonathan J. Levin in Mexico City at 
 jlevin20@bloomberg.net ;  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
